76561198012931848,Not Recommended,325420,25281306,"Posted: 1 September, 2016",all,ThomJ,"TL;DR,DESPERATELY NEEDS A MIRROR MODE, otherwise it's pretty good.Recent updates have made this game a little more enjoyable for me, but I'm still getting frustrated with the fact there's noMIRROR MODE, and i'll probably sound like a broken record throughout this review but that's really the only thing preventing me from reccomending this.BuilderI only really enjoy building planes, but that's not the games fault, i'm just not interested in building cars. One of my biggest gripes is that there's noMIRROR MODE.You want to build a twin engined plane? You'll have to build the engine twice. You want to put windows on it? You'll have to build them twice. You want a gear retraction mechanism? You'll have to bui..you get the point. It makes EVERYTHING more tedious and difficult than it should be. I've spent hours trying to build and ""skin"" an aircraft only to find that the skin plate on one side was like, one notch off. IF THERE WAS AMIRROR MODE, I wouldn't have even had that problem in the first place, or at least, it would have been easier to fix. But instead it took me another 2 hours just to nail down what exactly was wrong and pretty much re-adjust every single other skin plate in order to fix it. I don't know why this feature has not been made a priority, it seems like it's pretty standard with most other creative building games.Aviation PartsWhile recent updates have brought several new types of wings (two to be specific), it still feels as though the selection is lacking. The adjustable wing is a good idea, but the way it's currently implemented basically forces you to put a skin over it (unless you don't care what your plane looks like) and also create somewhat complicated systems to add basic flight controls, which of course you have to do twicebecause there's still no MIRROR MODE.The other issue of which i'm not sure whether or not it's a bug, but the amount of lift generated doesn't change with the wing's size, or at least the indicator doesn't change. You can also only change the wings shape in two directions so you are basically stuck with a rectangular wing, not a huge issue but I wish it was more flexible like the directional plates. It feels very much like a place holder.The other wing that was added was the ""invader"" wing. It's cool, but I won't get much use out of it just because it's so large and doesn't really fit with the types of planes I want to build, a very minor and personal complaint.That being said, I do appreciate the addition of the two new types of propellers. I haven't had time to play around with them very much but they do appear to have benefits and drawbacks (as opposed to the standard and supersonic props) and are not just purely asthetic.BugsI didn't find as many bugs when I played it this time, granted I only played for about 2 hours so it's possible I missed some. The only one I really found was the issue with the adjustable wings not updating the lift indicator.UPDATE! The lift indicator is a bug and it updates after you load another vehicle and then reload the one that has the adjustable wings. Also! After two hours of skinning an aircraft, the game crashed without any warning or error mesage and I lost two hours of progress. It's a real shame thatTHERE'S NO MIRROR MODEbecause now I have to spend ANOTHER two hours skinning the same exact thing. Great! I suggest adding an autosave function to avoid this situation in the future. Or, you know, add aMIRROR MODEso it doesn't take as long to recover. Was looking forward to actually testing my plane but nope!EARLY ACCESSThis game has been in alpha for almost two years. Really? It's another example of an early access game that just never leaves this state, or if it does, it's at the expense of the player base (see SpaceBase DF9). If I had to make a guess, it will never leave alpha (PROVE ME WRONG COPY-BUG-PASTE!), that just seems to be the trend of early access games these days. Updates have become more frequent now which I really do appreciate, I think that was a step in the right direction. Some features are taking a ridiculous amount of time to implement fully though, such as multiplayer. It was introduced in late June of 2016 but it still says ""experimental"" on the button? Have you guys just forgotten to change that or is it actually still experimental?The Good NewsIf you have the paitence to learn how to build and to do the actual building, it's actually pretty enjoyable. There's nothing more rewarding than building something that works just the way you want it to. Making small adjustments and tweaks to fine tune your ""creation"" is surprisingly fun. Even being frustrated with it at times I still find myself craving to build something new. The physics has been improved since HB13 and while it's certainly a long ways from being considered ""realistic"", it feels good for what it is and most importantly, it's fun. It's no X-Plane 10, but the aerodynamics are decent too.SummaryHonestly at this point, the game is just about worth what the developer is asking for but I'm still waiting for aMIRROR/SYMMETRY MODEto be added(SERIOUSLY GUYS, THIS NEEDS TO BE PRIORITY ONE, WEAPONS CAN WAIT).It's such a basic tool that saves everyone hours of needless building and yet I haven't heard so much as a peep about such a tool being in the works. If it's been mentioned somewhere on the forums that I've missed, please let me know. Only once that's added can I reccomend this game to others, but it'll still need some work before I can truly fall in love with it."
