76561198099050961,Recommended,325420,17727313,"Posted: 26 August, 2015",all,Aspiring Wackjob,"Is this game one I would recommend? Yes. Are there some problems with it? Of course, it's still an early access title. It's much more optimized, so it can definitely be played on some slightly lower end PCs. I use my Xbox 360 controller for vehicles, which makes things a bit easier on me. You have lots of options as to what to build (and there is still more to come). I've built everything from small 110cc powered boats to hypersonic jets that can go past 7,400 km/h before hitting the world border (took me 3 days of continuous testing and improvement.The one thing people don't get about physics and this game is that this is not something you'd find in Forza, NFS, GTA or CoD. This is all about solid and fluid dynamics. It's about what you can do to improve the quality of whatever you build. Build it faster, stronger, more efficient. This is something that takes practice, not something you can just pick up and go. But, once you do get the hang of it the possibilities are nearly endless. I just hope they make longer runways and bigger worlds. My hypersonic jet can go much faster than 7.4k km/h."
