,Recommended,325420,15685802,"Posted: 4 May, 2015",all,SuperKai64,"HomeBrew, It's pretty much a game where you make ""stuff"" (and I say that because its to broad to specify).You can litterally make anything you want, hovercrafts, helicopter boats and more. It's even got multiplayer and for a game this new this is awesome.You may be thinking ""Oh I played other sandbox games like GMod"" but HomeBrew is different;-The map is HUGE, and that is no exaduration either-You can make your own parts (Pipes for all you MLG's out there) allowing you to make any vehicle you can imagine-Proper sandbox, none of this ""Oh you can spawn stuff in. SANDBOX GAME!""-No BS mods required to make it fun, its got it all (Including weapons :P)-Advanced design engine, the way you design things is simple and easy to get for sandbox vehicle builder meaning you dont have to google tons of videos to find out how to use it-Information, you dont have to but you can read about every parts origin (History lesson in a game!)-No lag, it may say it needs 3 cores to run, but it really doesnt it runs great at decent settings on my dual core laptop with dated graphics card (I have better ones, I ain't no scrub!)-""123 No lag for me"" cheat command takes you to a less laggy world even if you do have issuesBy no means am I saying this game is the king of all sandboxes, but if want to design things and test them with your ""friends"" then this is the game for you.Bad things about this game (even though you read this far in a posative review)-Can be labourious at times, such as wielding a part rather than a quick place without having to do multiple clicks, but for Beta I can accept this-Not many parts, again  I reviewed this when it was EARLY ACCESS but the amount the game gives you is sufficient to keep you occupied (Not saying that there isnt enough, rather theres thinds I'd like to see in the future E.g. Stairs)-Graphics outside the valley can be a little lacking such as ""streched"" textures but its not frustrating you dont need to leave the valley unless you are using the ocean (water does look nice tho)-Getting round the map, sometimes this can be fun such as making the player use vehicles they have made, but if you just want to use a new boat you've made then you have to go quite some distance to get to it.I dont want to knock this game for what it is right now, to be fair you couldnt tell this was a Beta release from what it is now.-S.C"
,Not Recommended,325420,26642826,"Posted: 17 November, 2016",all,Ottomic,"Homebrew is a vehicle building game where its worst feature is the vehicle building.The graphics are okay, the sounds are... ehh, the prebuilt vehicles are *awesome*, the game world is huge and varied and the idea of building the stuff of your dreams is enticing enough to get you to build.And then you realize how sucky building is.For starters, the builder has physics on it, meaning every part that's not tied to the starting node will fall to the ground and tumble, making you adjust your camera, go around to the face you want to weld to your vehicle, click it, and then back to the vehicle to select the part to weld it to. It has no symmetry tools either, which will force you to do each thing twice for the other side of it. You can build custom pipes which is great in theory but then you realize you have to do it *again* for every single one you build. On top of that, parts are throughly premade and scaling is almost non existant, limited to a handful of *components* (not whole parts), and the few that include rescaling only allow for very limited options (you can make a rectangular  wing wider and longer, but not change its shape). You can't move stuff easily either, if you want to shift a set of parts sightly forward or backward you will have to disconnect the root part which will make EVERYTHING disconnect from each other and fall to the ground. The selection of parts is adequate, but with fixed dimensions and with the busywork of having to do symmetry manually the frustration will quickly set in.You do link parts manually, which is great, letting you make very complex inner workings, and stuff like gears and logical connectors also opens up a lot of ideas, but the game sorely lacks a lot of the basic building blocks that would make such a product enjoyable and accessible.3/10. The building really mares this game down to the point of unpleasantness, and though the more advanced options are really juicy looking, making anything in this game is an exercise in busywork, unpleasantness, and frustration. It has advanced very little since I tried it out a year or so ago, and it has no excuse for being this intensely clunky in a world where games like KSP and Empyrion exist."
76561198040335732,Recommended,325420,31908368,Posted: 22 May,all,RhoSigma,"Well i figured it's probably about time i reviewed Homebrew since i'm almost at the 2000 hour mark.Attachers pls.-fin-Just kidding (not kidding about the attachers though).An awesome little game as it is already and still has lots of development to go. And so far the only game i've successfuly made a fully mechanical helicopter in, with an entirely mechanical, physics based swashplate mechanism that's beautifully stable even at 340 RPM plus.The game certainly has it's rough edges but the devs have always been focused on improving the game, having known the developers and spoken to a few of them almost daily for some time now it's clear that Homebrew isn't just about money, it's something they're honestly passionate about. They're always doing their best to keep in touch with the community and work from feedback, and while they're sometimes notthe bestdevs out there*cough* niv overwriting iggy's work *cough*, they make up for it in their commitment to the game and it's community.Which makes a good seguae to the community side of Homebrew. Homebrew's community is honestly the best i've ever been in, albeit it small it's extremely friendly and helpful.The content of the game can be a bit minimal as-is for people not so inclined to create and share vehicles, but that will change after the addition of weapons to the game, which are being developed at the time of this review.TL;DRGreat game, albeit missing an objective currently which will change in the near future. Awesome developers, a few of which i've become friends with. Great, friendly, helpful community, including in-game and in Discord. I'm 2000 hours in and have thousands more ahead no doubt.Also, you can throw toilets you made yourself past the sound barrier and into the next continent with a catapult you made yourself. What's not to love?"
