76561198022294475,Recommended,325420,12954205,"Posted: 15 November, 2014",all,Tiearian,"Overall, this game has alot of potential. Though at its current state, its not very detailed, in the way the mechanics work. If this is changed, then this could become a very fun tool to create new ideas in. Though at the moment, it feels more like a lego game.The Tutorial System Is very odd, and brief. Though if you can notice the little ""?"" Icon, there is more detail within it.Unfortunatly, when you finally finish creating something, it doesn't react the way you wanted it to, at all. Not because you failed at realizing the physics engine, but because it just isn't indepth as it needs to be.Physics, are, well to say the least, quite bad. For instance, If you were to make a basic plane, put four wings on it, and One Prop, and go full RPM, you will just go up in the air, and spin chaoticly in circles. Also there is no individual part physics involved. What I mean by this, is it doesn't seem like the prop (for instance) has its own weight, causing it to have no centrifugal force. Meaning there is no torque/pressure rotation in the given direction the prop is spinning from.- Aswell, as there is no way to view (while building your vehicle) where the weight lies within the vehicle parts and/or the completed vehicle. Which partially leads me to believe, that the weight is only cut into a hand full of segments on your final vehicle, instead of each part having its own weight. Now this may not seem big now, but it will make a significant difference of  a realisitic inventive experiences, down the road.- Due to the lack of realistic physics in this game, It makes your inventions feel... well, not so inventive. More like you've put some lego together(for an hr or two) and then started running around your room going... VROOOOOM!!! (not saying those weren't epic times, Just saying theres a time and place, and this isn't it.)The Keyboard layout, is boarder line. There are some odd keys like, P & M, that adjust your given throttle. Where R & F, would be significantly more suitable. (In opinion)HowEVER, if they can fix these things in updates, then it will become very rewarding. Though at the moment, when you are finaly done your craft/vehicle, the reward is very underwhelming.The way this Game sits, it should be roughly $9.99 CAD. Not $19,99.Future Updates, like Gear boxes, and/or Gear Systems, and 360 Degree hinges, Would add much more diversity. And of course, a better physics engine. :)"
